\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {2.3}{\ignorespaces A plot of the matter power spectrum at redshift $z = 0$ with varying fraction of cold dark matter density $\Omega _\mathrm  {c}$ and varying Hubble parameter $h$. The power spectrum is obtained using the CLASS Boltzmann solver \citep {lesgourgues2011cosmic}. Notice the the power specturm peaks at a scale equivalent to the Hubble scale at the matter-radiation equality. Furthermore, the wiggles in the power spectrum are due to the sound waves that popagates in the baryon-phton fluid due the contrasting force of the fluids's pressure and gravity.}}{19}{figure.caption.4}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{theory_fig:power_spectrum_varying_params}{{2.3}{19}{A plot of the matter power spectrum at redshift $z = 0$ with varying fraction of cold dark matter density $\Omega _\mathrm {c}$ and varying Hubble parameter $h$. The power spectrum is obtained using the CLASS Boltzmann solver \citep {lesgourgues2011cosmic}. Notice the the power specturm peaks at a scale equivalent to the Hubble scale at the matter-radiation equality. Furthermore, the wiggles in the power spectrum are due to the sound waves that popagates in the baryon-phton fluid due the contrasting force of the fluids's pressure and gravity}{figure.caption.4}{}}
